$ SQL Server: dynamic management views and functions
@ dynamic management views and functions

Dynamic management views and functions allow a → development/databases/DBA to check the health and state of an → development/databases/SQL-Server/architecture/instance[SQL Server instance] and
its → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/database[databases].
-
In order to query instance related information, the *view server state* permission is required, for database related information, the *view database state*.


The names of dynamic manamagement views and functions start with the prefix `dm_` and belong to the → development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys[sys schema], see
→ development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/views/dm[`dm_*` views] and
→ development/databases/SQL-Server/administration/schemas/sys/objects/functions/dm[`dm_*` functions].
